tr: a group of sheep or goats
a church congregation guided by a pastor
(often followed by `of') a large number or amount or extent
example: he made a mint on the stock market
see the rest of the winners in our huge passel of photos

tr: come together as in a cluster or flock
example: The poets constellate in this town every summer

tr: move as a crowd or in a group
example: Tourists flocked to the shrine where the statue was said to have shed tears

value.def: A flock of birds, sheep, or goats is a group of them.

example.ex: They kept a small flock of sheep...
They are gregarious birds and feed in flocks.
example.tran: 它们是群居鸟类，会集群觅食。

value.def: You can refer to a group of people or things as a flock of them to emphasize that there are a lot of them.

example.ex: These cases all attracted flocks of famous writers.
example.tran: 这些案件都吸引了大批知名作家的关注。

value.def: If people flock to a particular place or event, a very large number of them go there, usually because it is pleasant or interesting.

example.ex: The public have flocked to the show...
example.tran: 公众蜂拥而至观看演出。

example.ex: The criticisms will not stop people flocking to see the film...
example.tran: 批评的声音不会阻止人们涌到影院观看这部电影。

example.ex: His greatest wish must be that huge crowds flock into the beautiful park.
example.tran: 他最大的愿望一定是希望人们成群结队地到这个美丽的公园参观。

value.def: A clergyman's flock is the group of Christians who come to his church or live in the area that he has responsibility for.
value.tran: (到牧师所在教堂做礼拜或属于其辖区的)全体教徒，教众群体
